---
// oxlint-disable-next-line no-unassigned-import
import '../styles/global.css';
import SiteNav from '../components/SiteNav.astro';
import SiteFooter from '../components/SiteFooter.astro';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <meta name="description" content="Terms of Use for sp00ky." />
    <title>Terms of Use — sp00ky</title>
  </head>
  <body class="min-h-screen flex flex-col">
    <SiteNav activePath="/terms" />

    <main class="flex-1">
      <section class="relative pt-24 pb-8 md:pt-32 md:pb-12 overflow-hidden">
        <div
          class="absolute inset-x-0 top-0 h-[420px] pointer-events-none"
          style="background: radial-gradient(60% 50% at 50% 0%, rgba(124,106,239,0.12), transparent 70%);"
        ></div>
        <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 relative z-10">
          <div class="mb-5">
            <span class="inline-block px-3 py-1 text-[10px] font-medium text-text-muted bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-full uppercase tracking-widest">
              Legal
            </span>
          </div>
          <h1 class="text-section md:text-hero font-semibold text-text-primary mb-4 tracking-tight">
            Terms of Use
          </h1>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-muted">Last updated: April 23, 2026</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="pb-24 md:pb-32">
        <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4">
          <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none text-text-tertiary leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              These Terms of Use govern your use of the sp00ky website, documentation, open-source
              library, and any managed cloud services offered under the sp00ky name (collectively,
              the "Service"). By accessing or using the Service, you agree to these Terms. If you
              do not agree, do not use the Service.
            </p>

            <h2>1. Use of the Service</h2>
            <p>
              You may use the Service for any lawful purpose, subject to these Terms. You are
              responsible for your use of the Service and for any content, code, or data you
              submit, publish, or display through it. You agree not to use the Service in a way
              that violates any applicable law, infringes the rights of others, or interferes with
              the Service's operation.
            </p>

            <h2>2. Accounts</h2>
            <p>
              Some parts of the Service require an account. You are responsible for keeping your
              credentials secure and for any activity that occurs under your account. Notify us
              immediately of any unauthorized use.
            </p>

            <h2>3. Open Source License</h2>
            <p>
              The sp00ky library is provided under its published open-source license, which
              accompanies the source code. Nothing in these Terms modifies the rights granted
              under that license.
            </p>

            <h2>4. Intellectual Property</h2>
            <p>
              The Service, including its branding, design, and documentation, is owned by sp00ky
              and its licensors. Except for rights expressly granted to you in these Terms or in
              the applicable open-source license, all rights are reserved.
            </p>

            <h2>5. Acceptable Use</h2>
            <p>
              You agree not to: (a) reverse engineer, circumvent, or disrupt the Service; (b)
              attempt to gain unauthorized access to systems or data; (c) send malware or unlawful
              content through the Service; or (d) use the Service to infringe the intellectual
              property or privacy rights of others.
            </p>

            <h2>6. Disclaimer</h2>
            <p>
              The Service is provided "as is" and "as available" without warranties of any kind,
              whether express or implied, including warranties of merchantability, fitness for a
              particular purpose, and non-infringement. sp00ky does not warrant that the Service
              will be uninterrupted, error-free, or secure.
            </p>

            <h2>7. Limitation of Liability</h2>
            <p>
              To the maximum extent permitted by law, sp00ky and its contributors will not be
              liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, or
              any loss of profits, revenues, data, or goodwill arising from your use of the
              Service.
            </p>

            <h2>8. Termination</h2>
            <p>
              We may suspend or terminate your access to the Service at any time if we believe
              you have violated these Terms. You may stop using the Service at any time.
            </p>

            <h2>9. Changes to These Terms</h2>
            <p>
              We may update these Terms from time to time. When we do, we will update the "Last
              updated" date above. Your continued use of the Service after changes become effective
              means you accept the updated Terms.
            </p>

            <h2>10. Contact</h2>
            <p>
              Questions about these Terms? Open an issue on our
              <a href="https://github.com/mono424/sp00ky" class="text-text-primary underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub repository</a>
              or reach out on
              <a href="https://discord.com/channels/902568124350599239/1454620262526877696" class="text-text-primary underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Discord</a>.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <SiteFooter />
  </body>
</html>
